The Special Adviser to Governor Aminu Tambuwal of Sokoto on Media and Publicity, Malam Imam Imam is dead.
Imam died at about 3.00.am at the Nziamye Turkish Hospital, Abuja, after a brief illness on Friday.
The younger brother, Abubakar Imam, and his friend, Muhammad Isa, confirmed that the deceased would be buried at Wuse 2 after Jumuat Prayers.
The burial would be held at the Al-Nur Mosque in Abuja.
The Sokoto State Government is yet to release a statement on the death of the governor’s media aide.
Meanwhile, Governor Aminu Masari of Katsina State has condoled with Sokoto State Government over the death of the Special Adviser to Gov. Aminu Tambuwal, on Media and Publicity, Imam Imam.
Masari in a statement by his Senior Special Assistant on Media and Publicity, Abdu Labaran, on Friday in Katsina, described the news of Imam’s death as sad.
“Imam is a bright and jovial young man who fully lived up to the lofty standard of his principal,’’ he said.
